&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 big thing:&lt;/strong&gt; Axios is seeking an execution-focused Director of Accounting to lead accounting operations, monthly close, treasury, tax, audit, compliance, and finance systems as our business and finance function continues to scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why it matters: &lt;/strong&gt;Strong accounting operations create the foundation for faster, clearer, and more reliable business decisions. This role will help ensure our financials are accurate, audit-ready, and built to support continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Go deeper:&lt;/strong&gt; This role sits on our Finance team, manages one direct report, and partners closely with FP&amp;amp;A, Payroll, Revenue Finance, department leaders, and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the monthly close process, including close timelines, journal entries, reconciliations, accruals, fixed assets, and close reporting packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accounting policies, procedures, controls, chart of accounts governance, and operational documentation to support accurate and scalable financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee AP, procurement, vendor management, contractor payments, cash management, bank reconciliations, 13-week cash forecasting, and treasury operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage bank access, fraud prevention, and accounting control processes to ensure strong financial governance and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance leadership to improve cash visibility, working capital management, and accounting operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead external audit coordination and oversee tax, sales and use tax, and related compliance processes with external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and improve accounting systems, integrations, workflows, data integrity, SOPs, and business continuity documentation across finance operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive automation, AI adoption, and process improvements to improve efficiency, scalability, accuracy, and controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with FP&amp;amp;A, Payroll, Revenue Finance, and business leaders to support forecasting, reporting, and operational decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop accounting team members while fostering a collaborative and high-performing team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The details:&lt;/strong&gt; Ideal candidates will demonstrate most of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of progressive accounting experience, including ownership of month-end close, audit, tax, treasury, internal controls, and accounting operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of GAAP, accrual accounting, balance sheet management, AP, cash management, and financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing accounting operations in a fast-paced, scaling organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ERP systems and finance process automation; Sage Intacct experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading audits and managing relationships with external tax and accounting advisors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with sales and use tax, state filings, nexus considerations, and compliance workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, project management, and process improvement skills, including leveraging systems, automation, AI, and workflow redesign to improve accounting operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel and Google Sheets proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, cross-functional partnership, and stakeholder management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and developing team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-accountability, execution-oriented mindset with comfort operating in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
